        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 3 at 10:41PM CDT by NWS Paducah KY</headline>
        <description>At 1041 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 9
miles north of Mayfield, moving east at 55 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Calvert City, Birmingham Ferry Recreation Area, Benton, Grand Rivers,
Hillman Ferry Campground, Symsonia, Reidland, Mayfield, and Land
Between The Lakes Area.

This includes the following highways...
Interstate 24 in Kentucky between Mile Markers 15 and 33.
Interstate 69 in Kentucky between Mile Markers 23 and 51.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
